{"id":"1107.4373","submitter":"Peter McNamara","authors":"Peter R. W. McNamara and Stephanie van Willigenburg","title":"Maximal supports and Schur-positivity among connected skew shapes","comments":"24 pages, 4 figures. Incorporates referee's suggestions; to appear in\n  the European Journal of Combinatorics","journal-ref":"European Journal of Combinatorics, 33 (6) (2012), 1190-1206","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The Schur-positivity order on skew shapes is defined by B \\leq A if the\ndifference s_A - s_B is Schur-positive. It is an open problem to determine\nthose connected skew shapes that are maximal with respect to this ordering. A\nstrong necessary condition for the Schur-positivity of s_A - s_B is that the\nsupport of B is contained in that of A, where the support of B is defined to be\nthe set of partitions lambda for which s_lambda appears in the Schur expansion\nof s_B. We show that to determine the maximal connected skew shapes in the\nSchur-positivity order and this support containment order, it suffices to\nconsider a special class of ribbon shapes. We explicitly determine the support\nfor these ribbon shapes, thereby determining the maximal connected skew shapes\nin the support containment order.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Jul 2011 20:29:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Mar 2012 15:38:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-07-11"}
